{"_id":"6YmYNdNpQH5ZrIWE","name":"The Cloak","type":"gift","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/icon-gift.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Talia the Sleeper","source":"The Broken Ones","category":"hunter","contentKey":"don1.talia-the-sleeper","ownerKey":"cazador.talia-the-sleeper","role":"gift","sequence":1}},"system":{"description":"Y our large nun’s cloak floats to defend you from \nthe world and contains many small items that you can manipulate. \nThanks to this Gift you are able to float and hover in the air, but \nalways at a speed equal to the pace of a human. Once per Scene, \nyou may:\n1. Hide an object inside your cloak, hiding it from everyone (even \nwhen searching through magic).\n2. Extract from your cloak an object that you need. It can be rare \nand peculiar, but not magic or unique.","notes":"See bt-tbo-sheets-eng-final-screen [2022-06-14].pdf, pages 24.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"owner":"Talia the Sleeper","source":"The Broken Ones","category":"hunter","key":"don1.talia-the-sleeper"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241650,"modifiedTime":1783973241650,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"DjG1TOTxy9sJWAl8","name":"In the Dream","type":"gift","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/icon-gift.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Talia the Sleeper","source":"The Broken Ones","category":"hunter","contentKey":"don2.talia-the-sleeper","ownerKey":"cazador.talia-the-sleeper","role":"gift","sequence":2}},"system":{"description":"Once per Scene, you can freely \ncommunicate with a subject who is unconscious through a \ndream. Alternatively, you may choose to spend 1 Soma to “read” \nthe dreams of a conscious subject. The Storyteller will reveal all or \npart of the subject’s Agenda to you through the narration of one \nof their dreams. Particularly powerful subjects and Hunters may \nrequire a Position Check to be able to capture their dreams.","notes":"See bt-tbo-sheets-eng-final-screen [2022-06-14].pdf, pages 24.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"owner":"Talia the Sleeper","source":"The Broken Ones","category":"hunter","key":"don2.talia-the-sleeper"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241650,"modifiedTime":1783973241650,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"QLU0VyhtrNJnULE5","name":"Gang","type":"gift","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/icon-gift.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"The Gang of three Pigs","source":"The Broken Ones","category":"hunter","contentKey":"don1.the-gang-of-three-pigs","ownerKey":"cazador.the-gang-of-three-pigs","role":"gift","sequence":1}},"system":{"description":"Y ou can act as three independent \ncharacters using all the same Descriptors, Gifts and \nSoma. Each gang member has 1 single Wound, for a \ntotal of 3. Each of you is skilled at something.\nThe eldest gains 1 Additional Success in actions \ninvolving repairing or tampering with the \nenvironment. \nThe middle brother gains 1 Additional Success in \nactions to construct or tamper with objects.\nThe youngest gains 1 Additional Success in actions \nnot related to any kind of obligation or duty towards \nthe gang or the current mission.","notes":"See bt-tbo-sheets-eng-final-screen [2022-06-14].pdf, pages 16.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"owner":"The Gang of three Pigs","source":"The Broken Ones","category":"hunter","key":"don1.the-gang-of-three-pigs"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241648,"modifiedTime":1783973241648,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"Y89zehE9ZTpYFFdH","name":"Eating the Divine","type":"gift","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/icon-gift.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"The Gang of three Pigs","source":"The Broken Ones","category":"hunter","contentKey":"don2.the-gang-of-three-pigs","ownerKey":"cazador.the-gang-of-three-pigs","role":"gift","sequence":2}},"system":{"description":"By eating the flesh, \nyou can regenerate your bodies and even return \nfrom death. At the end of each Scene, each member \nrecovers their Wound as long as at least one of the \nBrothers is still alive to activate the power of this Gift. \nOnce per Scenario, one of you can spend 1 Soma to \nheal immediately from 1 Wound and come back to \nlife instantly.","notes":"See bt-tbo-sheets-eng-final-screen [2022-06-14].pdf, pages 16.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"owner":"The Gang of three Pigs","source":"The Broken Ones","category":"hunter","key":"don2.the-gang-of-three-pigs"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241648,"modifiedTime":1783973241648,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"THbScmOrdMv8RZBN","name":"Light the Flame","type":"gift","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/icon-gift.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Yvonne of the Dark","source":"The Broken Ones","category":"hunter","contentKey":"don1.yvonne-of-the-dark","ownerKey":"cazador.yvonne-of-the-dark","role":"gift","sequence":1}},"system":{"description":"Y ou can manipulate fire, as \nlong as there is already a flame in the environment. \nDecide whether to increase or decrease its size or \nintensity, as well as the direction it burns. Y ou can \nalso manipulate the flame to hit something within \nnine feet of it. Y ou gain 1 Additional Success to each \naction you take while manipulating fire. The first time \nyou use this Gift in a Scene, the Storyteller may decide \nthat your action will spread the flames in some way.","notes":"See bt-tbo-sheets-eng-final-screen [2022-06-14].pdf, pages 26.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"owner":"Yvonne of the Dark","source":"The Broken Ones","category":"hunter","key":"don1.yvonne-of-the-dark"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241651,"modifiedTime":1783973241651,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"0rABW0VedKU8zMBv","name":"Innocent Smile","type":"gift","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/icon-gift.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Yvonne of the Dark","source":"The Broken Ones","category":"hunter","contentKey":"don2.yvonne-of-the-dark","ownerKey":"cazador.yvonne-of-the-dark","role":"gift","sequence":2}},"system":{"description":"When you talk to someone, \nyou can spend 1 Soma to provoke their sympathy (the \nStoryteller will evaluate whether or not the subject is \nsensitive to your influence) to create an Agenda in \nwhich the target feels somehow responsible for you. \nDuring a Scene, if the location is crowded, you can \nact or move without anyone noticing.","notes":"See bt-tbo-sheets-eng-final-screen [2022-06-14].pdf, pages 26.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"owner":"Yvonne of the Dark","source":"The Broken Ones","category":"hunter","key":"don2.yvonne-of-the-dark"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241651,"modifiedTime":1783973241651,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"HNUOTT0ELCLEHtOe","name":"Time Watches","type":"gift","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/icon-gift.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Hatta Carter","source":"The Broken Ones","category":"hunter","contentKey":"don1.hatta-carter","ownerKey":"cazador.hatta-carter","role":"gift","sequence":1}},"system":{"description":"When you want to use time to your \nadvantage, you can twist the stem on one of your watches and choose \nfrom the following. \n1. Slow the World Down: Receive 1 Additional Success to your \nnext Position Check.\n2. Speed up the Hatter: Y ou can act immediately (unless you \nhave already done so during the Exchange) by interrupting anyone’s \naction, regardless of what else might be happening in the narrative. \nWhen you use your watches, you gain 1 Time Token. During the \nScenario, the Storyteller can spend 1 Time Token to freeze you a few \nseconds in time and give you 2 Penalties to a Defense Check. If you \ntake an Interlude and drink some good tea, you can discard all the \nTime Tokens you have accumulated.","notes":"See bt-tbo-sheets-eng-final-screen [2022-06-14].pdf, pages 10.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"owner":"Hatta Carter","source":"The Broken Ones","category":"hunter","key":"don1.hatta-carter"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241647,"modifiedTime":1783973241647,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"T6W8MVlS2t13rQkV","name":"Playmates","type":"gift","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/icon-gift.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Hatta Carter","source":"The Broken Ones","category":"hunter","contentKey":"don2.hatta-carter","ownerKey":"cazador.hatta-carter","role":"gift","sequence":2}},"system":{"description":"Y ou own three automated dolls, The Little \nHatter, The Hare, and The Dormouse. Each automaton can perform \nsmall tasks, such as picking up and carrying items or delivering a \nmessage. Each doll has a special ability.\nThe Little Hatter can explode, inflicting 1 Wound to everyone \nwithin ten feet of it. \nThe Hare can always find a way, even through narrow places or \nclosed doors. \nThe Dormouse can fall asleep and deactivate to discard 1 Time \nToken. \nDuring Interludes, repair all automata.","notes":"See bt-tbo-sheets-eng-final-screen [2022-06-14].pdf, pages 10.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"owner":"Hatta Carter","source":"The Broken Ones","category":"hunter","key":"don2.hatta-carter"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241647,"modifiedTime":1783973241647,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"fzwj3zBsNNAjwcXx","name":"The Red Hood","type":"gift","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/icon-gift.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Iskra the Young Wolf","source":"The Broken Ones","category":"hunter","contentKey":"don1.iskra-the-young-wolf","ownerKey":"cazador.iskra-the-young-wolf","role":"gift","sequence":1}},"system":{"description":"Y ou can spend 1 Soma to look exactly like \na common child. Create a Descriptor that contains one of the words \nPretty, Small, or Sweet. As long as you maintain your disguise, no \nadult will notice you or consider you a potential danger. Receive 2 \nAdditional Successes to the first action you take when you decide to \ndrop your disguise and reveal who you are.","notes":"See bt-tbo-sheets-eng-final-screen [2022-06-14].pdf, pages 14.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"owner":"Iskra the Young Wolf","source":"The Broken Ones","category":"hunter","key":"don1.iskra-the-young-wolf"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241648,"modifiedTime":1783973241648,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"y4ej5KaKhKoaJSH6","name":"Pack","type":"gift","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/icon-gift.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Iskra the Young Wolf","source":"The Broken Ones","category":"hunter","contentKey":"don2.iskra-the-young-wolf","ownerKey":"cazador.iskra-the-young-wolf","role":"gift","sequence":2}},"system":{"description":"When you coordinate and act with one or more of your \nteammates against a common threat, you both get 1 Additional Success \nfor your Position Check. At the end of the Scene, if you have resolved \na significant issue thanks to the collaboration with your companions, \nyou recover 1 Soma.\nIwas abandoned by my mother in a large forest and survived by joining a pack of werewolves. After \na year of honing my predatory skills, I tracked down the woman I once called “Mother” and sank \nmy fangs into her throat. My pack was dismantled by a group of Hunters and the Order captured me.","notes":"See bt-tbo-sheets-eng-final-screen [2022-06-14].pdf, pages 14.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"owner":"Iskra the Young Wolf","source":"The Broken Ones","category":"hunter","key":"don2.iskra-the-young-wolf"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241648,"modifiedTime":1783973241648,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"398ofO7eaA9Wvvc1","name":"Mutant","type":"gift","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/icon-gift.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Bloodwhite","source":"The Broken Ones","category":"hunter","contentKey":"don1.bloodwhite","ownerKey":"cazador.bloodwhite","role":"gift","sequence":1}},"system":{"description":"Y ou start the Scenario with 3 Mutation Tokens. \nY ou may spend 1 Mutation Token to modify a part of your body, \nsuch as turning your arms into wings or your skin into a thick \ncarapace. Create a Descriptor that represents the mutation. Y ou \ngain 1 Additional Success whenever you take advantage of your \nmutation. Whenever you change shape, the Storyteller can decide \nthat the hormone emitted by your body bewilders the mind of an \nNPC nearby, creating a specific Agenda for them that leads them \nto seek you in some way. Y our mutations remain until the end of \nthe Scene. Once per Scenario, the Storyteller can declare that this \nGift is activated without you realizing it and give you 1 Mutation \nToken.","notes":"See bt-tbo-sheets-eng-final-screen [2022-06-14].pdf, pages 6.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"owner":"Bloodwhite","source":"The Broken Ones","category":"hunter","key":"don1.bloodwhite"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241646,"modifiedTime":1783973241646,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"NSHpPh5KwwMeHLdq","name":"Mutagenic Touch","type":"gift","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/icon-gift.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Bloodwhite","source":"The Broken Ones","category":"hunter","contentKey":"don2.bloodwhite","ownerKey":"cazador.bloodwhite","role":"gift","sequence":2}},"system":{"description":"Y ou can inflict 1 Wound to a living \nbeing with the touch of your hand. If you kill the target this way, \nit will explode in a gruesome way, scaring everyone present. The \nmost impressionable NPCs, at the Storyteller’s discretion, will \nthen try to avoid any confrontation with you. When you achieve \nan Outcome with an Increment with your touch and kill someone, \nyour body assimilates part of the exploded flesh, and you may \nrecover 1 Mutation Token or 1 Soma.","notes":"See bt-tbo-sheets-eng-final-screen [2022-06-14].pdf, pages 6.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"owner":"Bloodwhite","source":"The Broken Ones","category":"hunter","key":"don2.bloodwhite"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241646,"modifiedTime":1783973241646,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"k2fPQ4t08c1JCzeq","name":"The Tale","type":"gift","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/icon-gift.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Sherazade the Weaver of Tales","source":"The Broken Ones","category":"hunter","contentKey":"don1.sherazade-the-weaver-of-tales","ownerKey":"cazador.sherazade-the-weaver-of-tales","role":"gift","sequence":1}},"system":{"description":"Y ou start each Scenario with 3 Story Tokens. \nOnce per Scene, you may tell a short story. If you do, spend \n1 Story Token and declare a Keyword that appears in your \nnarrative, then mark it down on your Sheet. During the \nScenario, if a Keyword you have marked is introduced during \na Scene by the Storyteller (for example, the Keyword is Soldier \nand you come across Soldiers), erase the word to get 1 XP and \n2 Additional Successes for either your next action or that of \none of your allies. When you learn an interesting new story, \nyou receive 1 Story Token.","notes":"See bt-tbo-sheets-eng-final-screen [2022-06-14].pdf, pages 22.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"owner":"Sherazade the Weaver of Tales","source":"The Broken Ones","category":"hunter","key":"don1.sherazade-the-weaver-of-tales"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241650,"modifiedTime":1783973241650,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"EDSpX6a4QW9K4amc","name":"Words Like Honey","type":"gift","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/icon-gift.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Sherazade the Weaver of Tales","source":"The Broken Ones","category":"hunter","contentKey":"don2.sherazade-the-weaver-of-tales","ownerKey":"cazador.sherazade-the-weaver-of-tales","role":"gift","sequence":2}},"system":{"description":"Y ou can speak beautiful words \nto bring out a memory, an emotion, or a fear. Spend 1 Story \nToken and choose one Keyword. Each NPC or Hunter who \nhas listened to you and is connected to the Keyword will \nbe overwhelmed by their emotions and will have to create \na relevant Descriptor and keep it throughout the Scene. \nParticularly powerful subjects and Hunters who oppose your \npower may require a Position Check. Y our allies receive 1 \nAdditional Success in the first action they take when using \nany Descriptor created by this Gift.\nI am the greatest storyteller that has ever lived, having learned my skills after serving a \nwealthy sultan for many years. I can’t remember why I left, but I suddenly found myself in \nEurope, where I used my skills against the Order and the Hunters. After my defeat, I was \nforgiven, for it was clear to my jailers that a dark force had clouded my mind. I serve the Order \nto regain my freedom, but also to find the one who corrupted my heart, forcing me to do harm.","notes":"See bt-tbo-sheets-eng-final-screen [2022-06-14].pdf, pages 22.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"owner":"Sherazade the Weaver of Tales","source":"The Broken Ones","category":"hunter","key":"don2.sherazade-the-weaver-of-tales"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241650,"modifiedTime":1783973241650,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"x1O1AMb8kGJS0z5S","name":"Weaver of Destiny","type":"gift","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/icon-gift.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Morgana of the Lake","source":"The Broken Ones","category":"hunter","contentKey":"don1.morgana-of-the-lake","ownerKey":"cazador.morgana-of-the-lake","role":"gift","sequence":1}},"system":{"description":"Once per Scene, you can give a goal \nto an ally, such as Defeat that enemy or Retrieve that item. As \nlong as your ally acts to fulfill the destiny you have indicated to \nthem, they get 1 Additional Success to all their actions. However, \nif at the end of the Scene you have not achieved your goal, you will \nboth suffer 1 Wound due to the magical backlash of destiny. When \nfaced with one or more choices, you can spend 1 Soma and ask the \nUniverse to help you decide. Choose a Keyword such as enemy, \ndanger, or something else and the Storyteller will tell you which \nof the possibilities in front of you is the most related to the word \nyou have chosen.","notes":"See bt-tbo-sheets-eng-final-screen [2022-06-14].pdf, pages 18.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"owner":"Morgana of the Lake","source":"The Broken Ones","category":"hunter","key":"don1.morgana-of-the-lake"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241649,"modifiedTime":1783973241649,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"9mSJWBFqT2SqxSPS","name":"Illusion","type":"gift","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/icon-gift.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Morgana of the Lake","source":"The Broken Ones","category":"hunter","contentKey":"don2.morgana-of-the-lake","ownerKey":"cazador.morgana-of-the-lake","role":"gift","sequence":2}},"system":{"description":"Y ou may spend 1 Soma to create up to three \nillusions and move them as you like. Create a Descriptor that \nrepresents your illusions. Every illusion is a distortion of the \nvisual field. Y ou may make them more believable by adding 1 \nelement, choosing from between sound, smell, or tactility. Y our \nillusions are realistic, but they will be exposed if closely examined. \nAlternatively, you may spend 1 Soma to create three illusory \ncopies of yourself to confuse watchers. Y ou gain 3 Additional \nSuccesses for the first Defense Check you make. Y ou then subtract \n1 Additional Success (down to zero) for each additional Defense \nCheck you must take.","notes":"See bt-tbo-sheets-eng-final-screen [2022-06-14].pdf, pages 18.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"owner":"Morgana of the Lake","source":"The Broken Ones","category":"hunter","key":"don2.morgana-of-the-lake"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241649,"modifiedTime":1783973241649,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"fFp8xXwZ41UGIB6X","name":"Lies","type":"gift","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/icon-gift.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Wound. Carlo the LivingPuppet","source":"The Broken Ones","category":"hunter","contentKey":"don1.wound-carlo-the-livingpuppet","ownerKey":"cazador.wound-carlo-the-livingpuppet","role":"gift","sequence":1}},"system":{"description":"When you tell a lie, you can temporarily make it a \nreality. Create a Descriptor that represents your lie and concerns \nsomething about you that you pride yourself on, such as: I have the \nstrength of five men, or I can fly through the air. The Descriptor \nremains throughout the Scene, and you gain 1 Additional Success \nthe first time you use it for an action. Each time you make use of this \nGift you receive 1 Lie Token. Y our nose will grow in proportion \nto the amount of Lie Tokens you have. During the Scenario the \nStoryteller can spend 1 Lie Token to give you 1 Penalty on a Check, \ndescribing how your clumsy puppet body prevents you from \nperforming at your best. With every Lie Token spent, your nose \nshrinks closer back to normal.","notes":"See bt-tbo-sheets-eng-final-screen [2022-06-14].pdf, pages 8.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"owner":"Wound. Carlo the LivingPuppet","source":"The Broken Ones","category":"hunter","key":"don1.wound-carlo-the-livingpuppet"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241646,"modifiedTime":1783973241646,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"07DD9ZbyFdsQzyFd","name":"Always in the Middle of Trouble","type":"gift","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/icon-gift.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Wound. Carlo the LivingPuppet","source":"The Broken Ones","category":"hunter","contentKey":"don2.wound-carlo-the-livingpuppet","ownerKey":"cazador.wound-carlo-the-livingpuppet","role":"gift","sequence":2}},"system":{"description":"Once per Scene, \nwhen you face a danger or problem arising from a previous choice \nyou have made, you recover 1 Soma and get 2 XP . When you do \nwhat an NPC asks and trust them without asking questions, you \ncan discard 1 Lie Token.","notes":"See bt-tbo-sheets-eng-final-screen [2022-06-14].pdf, pages 8.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"owner":"Wound. Carlo the LivingPuppet","source":"The Broken Ones","category":"hunter","key":"don2.wound-carlo-the-livingpuppet"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241646,"modifiedTime":1783973241646,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"FZe4yw7cmoEqwr0U","name":"Physician","type":"gift","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/icon-gift.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Alice of Other Worlds","source":"The Broken Ones","category":"hunter","contentKey":"don1.alice-of-other-worlds","ownerKey":"cazador.alice-of-other-worlds","role":"gift","sequence":1}},"system":{"description":"Once per Scenario, when you take the \ntime to treat an injury, you may heal 1 Wound suffered \nby one of your patients, also bringing them back from \napparent death or unconsciousness. Y ou may spend 1 \nSoma to reassure and calm someone who is frightened or \nexperiencing any negative feeling. If you do, you receive \n1 Additional Success to any Check involving interactions \nwith that patient for the remaining of the Scenario.","notes":"See bt-tbo-sheets-eng-final-screen [2022-06-14].pdf, pages 2.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"owner":"Alice of Other Worlds","source":"The Broken Ones","category":"hunter","key":"don1.alice-of-other-worlds"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241645,"modifiedTime":1783973241645,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"6GWPdYyWedOX1p2K","name":"Cheshire the Lynx","type":"gift","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/icon-gift.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Alice of Other Worlds","source":"The Broken Ones","category":"hunter","contentKey":"don2.alice-of-other-worlds","ownerKey":"cazador.alice-of-other-worlds","role":"gift","sequence":2}},"system":{"description":"Cheshire is an NPC fully \nunder your control, with the following profile:\nOL Medium 5 – (2 Wounds) \nDescriptor: I am a big, short-tempered wild lynx and I only \nlive to serve Alice.\nGift - Two Souls: Y ou share your soul with Cheshire, and \nyou can see and feel through her senses. Y ou can spend \n1 Soma to make Cheshire immaterial for an action and \nallow her to cross any obstacle.","notes":"See bt-tbo-sheets-eng-final-screen [2022-06-14].pdf, pages 2.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"owner":"Alice of Other Worlds","source":"The Broken Ones","category":"hunter","key":"don2.alice-of-other-worlds"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241645,"modifiedTime":1783973241645,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"ixp1GR9k5NIfO7Bd","name":"The Beast","type":"gift","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/icon-gift.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Beauty and her Beast","source":"The Broken Ones","category":"hunter","contentKey":"don1.beauty-and-her-beast","ownerKey":"cazador.beauty-and-her-beast","role":"gift","sequence":1}},"system":{"description":"Dionysus is an NPC fully under your control, \nwith the following profile:\nOL Medium 5 – (Wounds: as Bella’s current value) \nDescriptor: I am a powerful and feral beastman. Only Bella’s scent \nkeeps me under control.\nGift - Monstrous: If he intends to kill someone, Dionysus may \nact twice in each Exchange. Once per Scene, Dionysus can break \nor lift even a large object with extreme ease. \nDuring Scenes, you decide how Dionysus acts. Any Wound one \nof you suffers also applies to the other. When Dionysus is within \na few steps, you receive 1 Penalty to each Check due to the strong \ndisgust you feel for him.","notes":"See bt-tbo-sheets-eng-final-screen [2022-06-14].pdf, pages 4.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"owner":"Beauty and her Beast","source":"The Broken Ones","category":"hunter","key":"don1.beauty-and-her-beast"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241645,"modifiedTime":1783973241645,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"dEKP4Pt4TPTUURQx","name":"The Beauty","type":"gift","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/icon-gift.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Beauty and her Beast","source":"The Broken Ones","category":"hunter","contentKey":"don2.beauty-and-her-beast","ownerKey":"cazador.beauty-and-her-beast","role":"gift","sequence":2}},"system":{"description":"Once per Scene, when you meet a new subject, \nyou may spend 1 Soma and declare that you have met them in the \npast and that you made some kind of deal with them. Create, in \nagreement with the Storyteller, an Agenda for them representing \nthe deal. If you take the time to talk to someone, the Storyteller \nmust reveal a clue about their current Agenda or a drawback of \none of their Descriptors. When someone shows a strong interest \nin you, Dionysus, if present, loses the use of the Monstrous Gift \nbecause of the strong jealousy and shame he feels for himself.","notes":"See bt-tbo-sheets-eng-final-screen [2022-06-14].pdf, pages 4.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"owner":"Beauty and her Beast","source":"The Broken Ones","category":"hunter","key":"don2.beauty-and-her-beast"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241645,"modifiedTime":1783973241645,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"vdBIvoFvOyi5Ca4O","name":"Ordog the Trusty Horse","type":"gift","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/icon-gift.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"The Knight with a Hundred Heads","source":"The Broken Ones","category":"hunter","contentKey":"don1.the-knight-with-a-hundred-heads","ownerKey":"cazador.the-knight-with-a-hundred-heads","role":"gift","sequence":1}},"system":{"description":"Ordog is a strange horseshaped entity. He can speak and is uncannily smart, but he is very \nsarcastic and capricious. Ordog will always know how to find you \nand will overcome all obstacles to reach you. When you ask for his \nhelp, Ordog will manifest his magical power and the Storyteller \nwill create a Descriptor that will allow him to do incredible things, \nsuch as fly or pass through the walls. The Storyteller has full \ncontrol of Ordog’s will and whims, so expect to have to promise \nhim something or convince him of your reasons.","notes":"See bt-tbo-sheets-eng-final-screen [2022-06-14].pdf, pages 12.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"owner":"The Knight with a Hundred Heads","source":"The Broken Ones","category":"hunter","key":"don1.the-knight-with-a-hundred-heads"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241647,"modifiedTime":1783973241647,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"TyAnyz31r1GLvqJk","name":"The Bridge","type":"gift","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/icon-gift.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"The Knight with a Hundred Heads","source":"The Broken Ones","category":"hunter","contentKey":"don2.the-knight-with-a-hundred-heads","ownerKey":"cazador.the-knight-with-a-hundred-heads","role":"gift","sequence":2}},"system":{"description":"When you protect a place or honor an oath \nyou have taken, nothing can overwhelm you. Once per Scene, you \nmay declare an oath in which you swear to defend something and \ngain 3 Oath Tokens. As long as you act to fulfill your oath, you can \nspend 1 Token to:\n1. Resist being separated from what you are defending.\n2. Gain 1 Additional Success for a Defense Check.\n3. Inflict 1 additional Wound to an enemy, but only if this allows \nyou to eliminate them. If you do, you must decapitate them. \nIf you break your oath, the magic that animates you weakens and \nthe Storyteller gains 1 Sleep Token that they can spend at any time \nto have you automatically fail a Check.\nThe Knight with \na Hundred\nHeads","notes":"See bt-tbo-sheets-eng-final-screen [2022-06-14].pdf, pages 12.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"owner":"The Knight with a Hundred Heads","source":"The Broken Ones","category":"hunter","key":"don2.the-knight-with-a-hundred-heads"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241647,"modifiedTime":1783973241647,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"bUfWhfKdllpgVzzl","name":"The Silver Shoes","type":"gift","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/icon-gift.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"OZena the Suffering","source":"The Broken Ones","category":"hunter","contentKey":"don1.ozena-the-suffering","ownerKey":"cazador.ozena-the-suffering","role":"gift","sequence":1}},"system":{"description":"When you move, you can teleport \nfor short distances, and this allows you to automatically elude \nany attempt to impede or prevent your movements. Y ou need to \nsee where you intend to reappear. If you’re holding someone’s \nhand, you can spend 1 Soma to bring them with you. Once \nduring the Scenario, you may make a longer trip, even of \nseveral miles, but only to a place that you have seen at least once \nbefore.","notes":"See bt-tbo-sheets-eng-final-screen [2022-06-14].pdf, pages 20.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"owner":"OZena the Suffering","source":"The Broken Ones","category":"hunter","key":"don1.ozena-the-suffering"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241649,"modifiedTime":1783973241649,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"9R6E7UYwYKjrFHPQ","name":"Experience of a Dark Journey","type":"gift","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/icon-gift.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"OZena the Suffering","source":"The Broken Ones","category":"hunter","contentKey":"don2.ozena-the-suffering","ownerKey":"cazador.ozena-the-suffering","role":"gift","sequence":2}},"system":{"description":"Y ou have \naccomplished many missions with strange companions and \nhave learned something from each of them. Y ou can invoke \neach of these effects once per Scenario.\n1. Tough as Tin: Ignore 1 Wound you should suffer from \nphysical damage. \n2. The Bravery of a Lion: Y ou gain 2 Additional Successes \nwhen you throw yourself against a great danger without caring \nabout the consequences.\n3. The Brain of a Genius Scarecrow: The Storyteller \nwill provide you with useful information about a place, \npersonality, or event you are dealing with. The information you \ngain is always useful to what you’re doing.\nI am a young American girl from 1939. Because of a magic tornado, I crashed into Broken Europe with a \nstrange doctor named Norman Henkle. I am suffering from a rare form of OZena, which disfigures my face \nand has blighted my life ever since I was a child. Dr. Henkle deceived me with the promise of a cure and a way \nback to my time, asking me to become a witch hunter. I committed crimes, even murders, until the Order put \nan end to my madness. I was forgiven and found in the Order a new home that I don’t want to run away from.","notes":"See bt-tbo-sheets-eng-final-screen [2022-06-14].pdf, pages 20.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"owner":"OZena the Suffering","source":"The Broken Ones","category":"hunter","key":"don2.ozena-the-suffering"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241649,"modifiedTime":1783973241649,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
